        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 9:41AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 940 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Beach Access Four, or near South Padre Island, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Port Isabel City Hall, U.s. Coast Guard Station, Port Isabel
Lighthouse, Beach Access Four, Port Isabel High School, Port Isabel
Fire And Police Department, South Padre Island Convention Center,
Beach Access Six, Laguna Vista Police Department, and Garria
Elementary School.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
